UI/UX Design Internship Task – Job Portal
Tool Used: Figma
Design Overview
The goal of this project was to design a clean and user-friendly job portal that helps users
easily discover jobs, view job details, and apply smoothly. The design focuses on clarity,
simplicity, and ease of navigation, especially for freshers and job seekers.
Design Flow
The user journey is designed as a simple and logical flow:
1. The user lands on the Main Page, where they can search for jobs and apply filters
such as location, job type, and experience level. And also, it contains job cards, that it
shows you can explore more jobs.
2. In that page we can see filter icon if you click on that an overlay will open then you
can see the location, job type and experience of the user.
3. By selecting a job card (UI/UX Design) in the Main Page, the user navigates to the
Job Description Page, which displays complete information about the selected role.
4. From the Job Description Page, the user clicks Apply Now to proceed with the
application.
5. After submitting the application, then an overlay opens and user sees a success
confirmation message that informs them about the next steps.
6. Then if you click back it shows a message about the user clarification or guides to the
next steps.
UX Decisions
• Filters are provided as a pop-up overlay to keep the main page clean while allowing
quick refinement of job results.
• Job cards are visually separated to make them easily scannable and clearly clickable.
• Important job information such as location, salary, experience level, and skills is
displayed in a structured and readable manner.
• The Apply Now button is highlighted to encourage action and guide the user toward
completing the application.
Application Process
Although the task did not mention an application form, a simple application form was
included to complete the job application flow smooth and UX thinking. After
submitting the form, a success message confirms that the application has been
submitted and informs the user about further communication.
This design aims to provide a smooth and intuitive job-search experience while
maintaining visual consistency and usability across all screens.
